  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Leading Cook",
  "description": "<p><strong>GOODWOOD PARK HOTEL SINGAPORE</strong></p>\n<p>One of Singapore’s most established Heritage Hotel and strategically located at Scotts Road, the Goodwood Park Hotel<strong> </strong>has celebrated its timeless elegance, legendary hospitality, and tradition of excellence. We are committed to building a high-performing team that is thoroughly engaged in achieving service excellence to exceed our guests' expectations.</p>\n<p>To continue the legacy of Goodwood Park, we are looking for dynamic and committed candidates to join our Food &amp; Beverage Department.</p>\n<p>Reporting to the Chef De Partie, your job responsibilities include, but not limited to:-</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Reports for duty punctually wearing the correct, clean uniform, shoes and name badge.</li>\n  <li>Maintains a good working relationship with colleagues within and outside the department.</li>\n  <li>Maintains cleanliness of refrigerators, cold room, working tables and kitchen equipment.</li>\n  <li>Supervises the various buffet set-up, replenishment and clearance and assists where necessary.</li>\n  <li>Supervises cooks on food preparation and assist them.</li>\n  <li>Ensure the cost-effective production of raw materials to minimize wastage.</li>\n  <li>Ensure the high quality of food preparation is in accordance with the established standard.</li>\n  <li>Ensure the electrical, mechanical equipment and utensils are in operation and properly maintained and to report on any malfunction.</li>\n  <li>Performs any other duties as may be assigned from time to time by the Management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Please be informed that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more information, visit www.goodwoodparkhotel.com</p>",
